I never watched a single episode of The Sopranos.

Amused by the recent JerseyMania that has swept over the Trashy Reality Show genre, after hearing several people, offline and on, assert that it all started with The Sopranos, I downloaded the first episode out of curiosity.

Since then, my life has been Officially on Hold. I am now Epically Behind on everything from laundry to returning phone calls and emails to work, because this show is television heroin.

A word of caution to those with slower connections.

If you did not watch The Sopranos when it was on HBO, pace yourself. 

Resist the temptation, if you can, to binge-gobble those first few seasons all at once, faster than you can download, and find yourself like me, staring impatiently at utorrent & jonesing for your next fix!

Thank You, big_dad_e, for your generosity in bestowing this magnificent gift upon earth residents. :)
